Ad Text:
About the Client:

Join a Private Equity-backed growing healthcare group at a pivotal stage of transformation, where you’ll help shape how the business plans, reports, and makes decisions. This is a newly created role with genuine scope to build the FP&A and performance reporting across a network of clinics.

About the Role:

Reporting to the CFO, this role offers the opportunity to shape and improve the group’s FP&A and performance reporting function. You’ll help design forecasting models, streamline and automate reporting, and deliver insight-driven analysis that supports smarter, more informed decision-making across the business.

You will also:

Lead budgeting, forecasting, and planning processes across the group
Design and deliver performance reporting, dashboards, and KPI frameworks in Power BI and Excel
Build and maintain driver-based financial models and rolling forecasts
Partner with business units to interpret performance, identify trends, and highlight risks and opportunities
Provide actionable insights and executive-level reporting for the CFO, CEO, and senior leaders
Collaborate with IT and data partners to enhance systems, data integrity, and automation
Drive continuous improvement in reporting, analysis, and performance management processes
Support scenario analysis, business cases, and investment evaluations
About You:

You’re either a commercially minded FP&A Analyst looking for a step up into a more senior role, or a hands-on Senior FP&A Analyst who is eager to build a role and function from scratch. You will enjoy working with data, modelling, and business partnering to deliver insight and drive performance, and thrive in a dynamic, growing environment where you can shape processes and influence decision-making.

You will bring:

CA/CPA qualified or working towards qualification
3 to 6 years’ experience in FP&A, commercial finance, or similar analytical roles
Strong experience in budgeting, forecasting, and driver-based financial modelling
Advanced Excel and Power BI skillset
Excellent communication and presentation skills for senior stakeholders
Proven ability to translate financial data into clear, actionable business insights
Experience in multi-entity or high-growth environments preferred
What’s on Offer:

Competitive salary in the range of $130,000 – $150,000 + super
Opportunity to influence and develop the FP&A function
High exposure to leadership and cross-functional collaboration
Flexible hybrid working arrangements
Supportive, growth-oriented culture focused on innovation and continuous improvement
Next Steps:
If this sounds like the next step in your career, please apply online today. For a confidential discussion, contact Campbell Hurry at c.hurry@4dtalent.com.au

Location: Canberra, ACT
Contract Type: Full-time Contract
Security Clearance: NV1 (must be an Australian Citizen and willing to upgrade to NV2 if required)

We are seeking a skilled and motivated Data and Business Analyst to support security clearance processes and operational efficiency within a high-profile government division. This role offers a unique opportunity to work at the intersection of data analytics and national security, contributing to improvements in vetting operations and executive decision-making.

Key Responsibilities:

Analyse multiple sensitive data feeds to identify patterns, trends and opportunities for improvement
Develop and maintain reports and dashboards to inform senior executive decision-making
Ensure reporting processes are accurate, complete and timely
Collaborate with stakeholders across the division to enhance analytic procedures and data governance
Contribute to change initiatives aimed at improving security operations and data management
Draft standard operating procedures for reporting and dashboard production
Undertake ad hoc data and business analysis tasks as required

About You:

Tertiary qualification in Information Technology, Data Analytics or a related field
Australian Citizen with a current NV1 security clearance and willingness to upgrade to NV2
Strong analytical and problem-solving skills
Proficiency in digital and data systems such as SQL and/or Power BI
Ability to engage in solution-focused discussions on data, systems and procedures
Excellent communication skills with the ability to translate complex data into actionable insights
High level of integrity and commitment to public service values

Please Note: This is a security-designated position. Applicants must hold a current Australian Government Negative Vetting Level 1 (NV1) Security Clearance prior to commencement.

Linda Jona
Consultant

Business Analyst - Finance Transformation

Location: Sydney, NSW (Hybrid - 3 days per week in office)
Contract Type: Day Rate Contract

About the Role

We're seeking a driven and experienced Business Analyst to join a finance transformation program within the financial services sector. This is a business-focused role - not a technology BA position - suited to someone with domain knowledge and a track record of delivering change across finance processes, reporting, and controls.

The successful candidate will play a key role in shaping and delivering improvements to processes, and systems, working closely with finance stakeholders to drive meaningful transformation.

Key Responsibilities

Partner with finance teams to analyse, document, and optimise business processes and workflows.

Lead requirements gathering and process mapping for finance transformation initiatives (e.g. GL, reporting, reconciliations, controls).

Define and document current-state and target-state processes, identifying improvement opportunities.

Collaborate with stakeholders to ensure business needs are captured and solutions are fit-for-purpose.

Support delivery and implementation of finance process and system changes (in partnership with technology where needed).

Develop and maintain business documentation including BRDs, process maps, test scripts, and training materials.

Support UAT, business readiness, and post-implementation review activities.

Provide actionable insights and recommendations to enhance finance efficiency and accuracy.

About You

Minimum 5+ years' experience as a Business Analyst within financial services (banking, insurance, wealth, or related).

Demonstrated experience in finance transformation or finance process improvement projects.

Strong understanding of finance and accounting processes - general ledger, reporting, month-end, reconciliations, and controls.

Excellent business analysis, documentation, and stakeholder management skills.

Ability to translate finance requirements into practical business outcomes.

Experience working in agile or hybrid delivery environments.

Proficiency in BA tools such as Confluence

Sydney-based and available to work 3 days per week onsite.

Contract Details

Start: ASAP

Duration: 12 months (potential extension)

Rate: Competitive day rate (commensurate with experience)

Location: Sydney CBD / Hybrid (3 days in office, 2 days remote)

Candidates MUST have full Australian work rights to be considered for this position.

Location: Sydney


At Prospa, we exist to unleash the potential of small business. We are building the future of small business and simplifying cashflow by building a leading platform that helps customers make payments, fund growth and reduce admin. Join us!

The role


As a Senior Data Analyst you will design, build, and standardise high‑quality data models and visualisations that drive decision‑making across Prospa. You will own the Power BI semantic layer, translate information models into efficient visualisations, and collaborate with business stakeholders to convert problems into actionable insights. You will champion data literacy as a data ambassador and continuously improve our analytics tool stack in Azure.

What you’ll be doing

Collaborate with product, finance, and business teams to define requirements and deliver BI solutions aligned with strategic goals.
Lead in-depth analyses to identify trends, risks, and opportunities, present insights through clear visualisations.
Own and optimise the Power BI environment, including modelling, performance, and governance.
Run workshops to clarify business problems, develop hypotheses, and recommend actions.
Build data models, write advanced SQL, and apply statistical techniques for decision support.
Define and enforce standards for visualisation, DAX, and modelling; document best practices.
Monitor and troubleshoot Power BI performance, connectivity, and refresh schedules.
Partner with Data Engineering, Product, and Finance to ensure consistent, business-ready data.
Promote data literacy and informed decision-making across the organisation.
Ensure BI solutions comply with governance, security, and privacy standards. Contribute to backlog grooming, sprint planning, and provide technical guidance.
What you’ll need to succeed

Proficiency with Power BI (DAX, Power Query/M, semantic modelling, performance optimisation).
Strong SQL and experience with analytics in Azure (e.g., Databricks or Snowflake).
Demonstrated ability to partner with business stakeholders and product teams to deliver impactful insights.
Deep understanding of data modelling principles and statistical analysis (A/B testing, regression, tree models)
Ability to translate information models, data dictionaries, and KPIs into efficient, intuitive visualisations.
Workshop facilitation and stakeholder engagement skills; strong written and verbal communication.
Ability to learn quickly and adapt in a fast‑moving environment, curiosity and continuous improvement mindset.
Good to have skills

Experience with dbt, Airflow, Python or R for data transformations and testing is highly desirable.
Experience working with Power BI Copilot and other AI tools to enhance analytics and reporting capabilities is highly desirable.
Knowledge of Power BI governance at scale (workspaces, deployment pipelines, RLS, usage analytics).
Familiarity with Databricks and PySpark.
Exposure to unit/integration testing of BI artefacts and data contracts.
Don’t let a confidence gap get in the way of submitting your application.
What we offer:


As a busy grow getter, our benefits are here to help you be unstoppable in your mission. Whether it’s a lofty career goal, investing in your family, saving the planet or simply feeling fulfilled:

Growth: There’s something for everyone including learning days, a learning allowance, leadership programs, CliftonStrengths workshops, digital learning, and biannual companywide learning weeks.
Wellbeing: Think fitness initiatives, seasonal programs (including flu shots, massages, skin checks, wellness classes), additional “Me Days” and access to holistic EAP coaching.
Lifestyle: Find your fit with flexible working options, top notch office facilities and diverse remote/ travel work options. You can also purchase additional leave and take up to 18 weeks paid parental leave.
Impact: Join a business that cares and is recertified as carbon neutral. And you can tap into volunteer days, our partnership with Kiva and join a range of employee resource groups.
Why Prospa?


We’re proud to be a certified Great Place to Work and recognised as a Best Workplace for Women, Best Workplace in Technology, and Best Workplace in Australia. We embrace diversity in people and ideas, fostering a collaborative, inclusive, and respectful environment where we celebrate who you naturally are.

Don’t just take our word for it, check out Prospa’s culture code to see it for yourself.

Job Title: Analyst – Tech M&A – Leading Global Investment Bank
Category: Corporate Finance & Investment Banking (Banking & Financial Services)
Ad Text:
Active pipeline of high-profile tech M&A transactions.
Opportunity to work directly with senior bankers across local and cross border transactions.
Dynamic platform with a strong growth trajectory in Australia.

‍

A leading global investment bank is seeking an Analyst to join its expanding Tech team. The firm has built a strong reputation advising high-growth and established technology businesses. 

This role offers the chance to work on complex public and private transactions within a high-performing team structure. You will gain direct exposure to senior clients and assist in end-to-end deal execution. The firm’s collaborative culture and commitment to developing junior talent ensure meaningful progression opportunities.

The ideal candidate will have 1-4 years’ M&A experience with strong analytical and financial modelling skills, sound commercial judgment, and a genuine interest in the technology sector. Candidates from investment banks, independent corporate advisory firms, or Big 4 Lead Advisory teams are encouraged to apply.

Apply now, or reach out to Toby Dickinson at for a confidential discussion.
